Make.Me.A.Bird. 

Because I wanted some company down there.

We ARE NOT the same. We ARE two different energies. Two different powers. Two different beings. EQUALLY responsible for maintaining the Divine balance of life in this dimension. EQUITABLY and abundantly equipped with abilities the other does not…and will never possess. EQUALLY and enthusiastically deliberate in reverence and respect of each other’s different gender roles….and, like she said… “Brave enough to assert the difference.”

PLEASE NOTE:
This is just my humble opinion. I’m not academically learned in Psychology. I’m not a theological scholar. I’m merely a slightly well-read nigga that’s fucked up some beautiful connections…and learned the lessons from the consequences that accompanied my bullshit.

David “Plug 2” Jolicoeur FOREVER. Rest, Brother… Rest.

12.5.2016.
@paradisoadam 

@wearedelasoul has been my absolute favorite hip-hop group since I first laid ears on ‘Plug Tunin’…mind blown. They spoke to and for the awkwardly smart and cool kids that commanded attention during high school lunch. You know…the stand alone swag original kids that bewildered the “fly” kids into envy and insecurity. They have (all)ways been a constant in my life’s soundtrack. I remember my Pop pulling up on me one day with ‘Stakes is High’ blasting from the 10 speakers in his conversation van… 
SON-“What up, Pop!”
POP-“I’m sick of bitches shaking asses. Sick of talkin’ ‘bout blunts. Sick of Versace glasses…” “This jawn is my chumpy!” He didn’t fuck with all my music but, he fucked with DeLa… 
Circa 2016… @callmekippy was too tired to go to the show because Snoota always turned up in the evenings, especially just before arriving on the planet. She was due in a couple weeks. Knowing they’re my favs, I was granted “on call” furlough to attend their show at @paradisoadam … I pull up to the back of the club (real niggas know) & run into @redmangilla …
RED- “ICE!!!! What up?!?! Wtf you doin’ here???”
ME- “lol…Moved here bout 2yrs ago…”
RED- “Do Mase’ and them know you’re here?”
ME- “I don’t think so… I’ve never met them…”
RED- “Fuck outta here… C’mon & hang stage right…”
Long story, tolerable… THEY KILL SHIT….DEAD….I mean, DEAD. Left us fans wanting nothing.
After the show, I walk in their dressing room…
DE LA- (in unison) “Black fucking Ice! What up!”
ME- (speechless for 30seconds)
ME- “How do y’all know me???”
MASEO- “C’mon nigga… What you mean, how…???”
Mind blown…
I get my fanboy shit out the way like I always do when I meet my influencers and inspirations. We kicked it for a while. Talked everything from bad weaves to the HAARP machine to them fighting German niggas in Berlin. 
They say, never meet your heroes… I’ve met most of mine and….well…. FUCK WHAT “THEY” SAY…. Meeting your heroes…depending on who your heroes are….is dope as fuck….especially when they have grown to appreciate your own contribution to the culture.
Thank you, Dave “Trugoy aka Plug 2” Jolicoeur…for adding to the artistic blueprint of my journey. We’ll link on Pluto.

Soooo, that night was much more epic than I initially remembered… My big brother, @richmedina was on the pleasure platters prior to the performance… My bro, @petephilly and his wife, @waytamonzon were in the energy… I was in my “gym rat” phase and recall…
WAYTA- “Heyyy, lovin’ this coat! (Wayta is a ferocious fashionista and fashion photo journalist)…and, how much bigger are you tryna get, Mar???” Lol. My bro, UK hip-hop royalty, @motetonline met up with me, as well… We were all stage right…which is a hella cramped space to share with a lotta niggas…no matter…we all Benjamin Buttoned 20yrs and had fun like teenagers…wait… I wasn’t a teenager 20yrs prior to the night… I was already a pop pop…wait….no, I wasn’t…. This math ain’t mathing right… I’m a writer,  damn it!!! Y’all know what the fuck I mean. It was a dope night. “Oooooh, oooooh, OOOOOOH…!!!” #delasoulforever #trugoythedoveforever #ghostweed #stakesishigh #paradisoamsterdam
Unconditional Love… It ain’t for the faint of heart.

(cont.)
This is where they smite 
His grace
and take swigs of sweet sorrow
and hopelessness 
with a shot of pain
for the chase…
This is where dreams end up
as staircase nightmares 
by the shotgun…
This is where the light 
dares not come…
It’s dark here 
but,
you feel the heat
when hammers spark here…
The pen is mighty 
but,
the Sword reigns…
So, watch ya talk, here.
Silhouetted in chalk, here.
Shots fired.
Fun deaded.
Kids running.
Look how fast the park clear!
Nigga, why you staring???
Watch ya gawk, here…
You’ll be next
with the paramedics 
leaning over,
yelling, “CLEAR!!!”
Yeah…
This is where the beasts roam
They walk about…
but, 
everybody silent, mayne…
Don’t nobody talk about…
The Unspeakable.

BE VERY VERY CLEAR, YOUNG BOY… WE AIN’T THE SAME.

My youngins get it f**ked up
When y’all talk about this game
Like 
it’s designed in their favor
Like 
it ain’t outlined for them
To waiver
Their rights 
For a little fame
Get in bullshit fights
For a little name
To get noticed by some niggas
That don’t give two f**ks
About you…
Until you make ‘em a few bucks
They doubt you…
Tell ‘em that you don’t do
The jives & shucks 
& they route you to the shelf
See, there’s no money
In good health
So, they need you to be 
Sick with it…
Ill content & delivery
Niggas
This nation thrives off misery 
Niggas
So, if you ain’t trying to let
Your hard times
Increase my wealth
Nigga…
Keep that progressive shit
To yourself…
This…
Is the business of buying souls
& we only f**k with those
Who tryna sell ‘em…
Ya see,
They may see me 
as an adversary 
Because they know
I’m tryna tell ‘em
About the forests of artists
Who grow
Only to meet industry axes
How they take a nigga dreams
&
Write ‘em off in they taxes…
Contracts are confusing
But, don’t worry…
They’ll appoint the lawyer
For you…
Whore you…
Loan you funds
To f**k your soul
Make you pay it all back
Yet
Still maintain control 
Of your stroll
Your tracks
& your hot ass slow flow
They’ll keep you lookin’ good
& all that
But, NO DOE…
When they get a bitch
They got a bitch…
—TLBI, ‘Exodus’ from ‘Real Talk’ @myfabolouslife
